        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(ui): rename chat sessions from the picker",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n- Chat/sidebar session picker had no inline rename capability. Users had to navigate to the Sessions table to rename a session, breaking their chat workflow.\n- Fix: Add inline session-title rename controls to the chat session picker/sidebar using the existing `sessions.patch` label contract. Preserve picker state during rename, block conflicting actions during save, and refresh picker/session lists without dropping loaded pages.\n- Scope: Control UI session picker only. Does not change the Sessions table, gateway rename API, or session metadata schema.\n\n## Evidence\n\n**Vitest:**\n```\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs ui/src/ui/views/chat.test.ts --run\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  123 passed (123)\n```\n\n**Browser proof** (real Chromium against local Control UI with mocked Gateway transport):\n\n![picker-open](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/3d0f75e2-3ab2-4d7e-ae3f-6493127e1d8e)\n![rename-editing](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/c0baa1f5-a0d1-423f-90a1-429a49c3f440)\n![rename-saved](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/3634e733-f17c-4ac7-b92f-e693c52443de)\n![rename-reopened](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/790e8f86-55e2-483f-9d01-43ca441ca8a5)\n\n**Video:** [session-picker-rename.webm](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/5a7f19ab-f79d-4d80-8381-ff1eee2f7850)",
        "branch": "fix/89922-session-picker-rename",
